        <div class="border-l-[3px] border-[#F59E0B] pl-6 py-5 bg-amber-50 rounded-r mb-6">
          <p class="text-sm font-black text-amber-600 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">THE BEFORE</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">Lakeview Wealth Management: $28M AUM, two advisors, Squarespace template from 2019. Looked professional but dated. "Good enough" thought partners. But prospects: visited website, saw template feel, questioned competency. High-net-worth prospects expected enterprise-grade digital presence. Lakeview looked like $10M AUM practice. 18 months: grew from $28M to $30M AUM. Organic growth: $2M. Prospects chose competitors with more professional websites. Partners stuck charging $8K minimums because site didn't justify higher.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-l-[3px] border-[#F59E0B] pl-6 py-5 bg-amber-50 rounded-r mb-6">
          <p class="text-sm font-black text-amber-600 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">THE FIX</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">Invested $12K in Webflow custom build with FINRA-compliant disclaimers on every page. Custom market commentary CMS for weekly insights. Client portal login prominently displayed in header. Team bios with credentials (CFP, CFA) and photos. Modern, enterprise-grade design. Build time: 3 weeks. Compliance review: passed with minor tweaks. Site felt like $100M+ AUM practice.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-l-[3px] border-[#F59E0B] pl-6 py-5 bg-amber-50 rounded-r mb-6">
          <p class="text-sm font-black text-amber-600 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">THE AFTER</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">18 months later: Lakeview grew from $30M to $42M AUM. That's $12M AUM growth in 18 months vs. $2M previous 18 months. 6x faster growth. Landed $3M client who found website, liked professional feel, booked discovery call. Raised minimums from $8K to $25K. Site justified 1% management fees. Partners finally charging what they're worth. Website investment: $12K. Return: $120K/year in additional recurring revenue (extra $12M AUM Ã— 1%). Paid for itself 10x over in first year.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-l-[3px] border-[#F59E0B] pl-6 py-5 bg-amber-50 rounded-r">
          <p class="text-sm font-black text-amber-600 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">THE 90-DAY BREAKDOWN</p>
          <ul class="text-gray-700 space-y-2 text-sm">
            <li><strong>Month 1:</strong> Webflow site launched with professional design and FINRA disclaimers. Inquiry quality improved immediately. 8 qualified inquiries vs. 3/month average. 2 new clients: $1.2M combined AUM. Revenue: +$12K/year recurring</li>
            <li><strong>Month 2:</strong> Market commentary CMS launched. Published 4 weekly insights. Organic traffic +340%. 12 qualified inquiries from content. 3 new clients: $2.8M AUM. Revenue: +$28K/year recurring</li>
            <li><strong>Month 3:</strong> Client portal login moved to header. Existing client engagement +67%. Referrals increased: happy clients refer more when engaged. 4 new clients: $3.5M AUM. 3-month total: $7.5M new AUM = $75K/year revenue. $12K investment paid back 6x in 90 days</li>
            <li><strong>Lesson:</strong> Professional website = perceived competence = AUM growth. High-net-worth prospects judge you by your digital presence. Template sites work for $10M AUM. Custom sites required for $50M+ AUM.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-6 pt-6 border-t-2 border-amber-200">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            <strong>The brutal truth:</strong> Your website justifies your management fees. If you're charging 1% on $1M+ portfolios, prospects expect enterprise-grade digital presence. Template site signals "small practice." Custom site signals "established firm." For financial advisors, design isn't vanityâ€”it's trust.
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mt-2">
            I rated Webflow 9.2/10 for advisors because custom FINRA disclaimers and professional design drive AUM growth. Start with Squarespace when building practice. Upgrade to Webflow when ready to scale to $50M+ AUM.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- THE HARD TRUTH -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-gradient-to-br from-red-50 to-orange-50">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 max-w-4xl">
      <div class="border-[3px] border-red-400 p-6 md:p-8">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-6">The Hard Truth About Advisor Websites</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-red-600 uppercase tracking-wider font-black mb-8">Mistakes that cost advisors millions in AUM growth</p>

        <div class="space-y-6">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-12 h-12 bg-red-500 text-white flex items-center justify-center font-black text-xl">1</div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-lg font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Template sites cap your AUM at $25M</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">High-net-worth prospects expect enterprise-grade digital presence. Template site signals "small practice" or "just getting started." RIA with Webflow custom site: $12M AUM growth in 18 months. Same-market RIA with Squarespace template: $2M AUM growth. 6x difference. Same market. Same approach. Different digital presence. Template sites work for starting. Custom sites required for scaling.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-12 h-12 bg-red-500 text-white flex items-center justify-center font-black text-xl">2</div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-lg font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Generic FINRA disclaimers = compliance risk</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">Compliance officer feedback: "Your site needs advisor-specific disclosures on each page." Generic footer disclaimer doesn't cut it. Webflow allows custom disclaimers tailored to page content. Squarespace templates limit placement. One compliance complaint = FINRA investigation = months of headaches regardless of intent. Custom disclaimer control isn't luxuryâ€”it's risk management.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-12 h-12 bg-red-500 text-white flex items-center justify-center font-black text-xl">3</div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-lg font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">No blog = 6x fewer qualified prospect inquiries</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">Advisor without blog: 41 inquiries in 12 months. Advisor publishing weekly market insights: 248 inquiries in 12 months. 6x difference. Why? People search for financial advice. They find your content. Then they reach out. Content marketing = authority = SEO = free qualified prospects. Paid ads = expensive leads. Blog = organic leads that convert better. Every advisor should blog weekly. Webflow CMS and Squarespace blog both work.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-12 h-12 bg-red-500 text-white flex items-center justify-center font-black text-xl">4</div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-lg font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Slow site speed = 43% lower conversion from qualified prospects</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">Tested: advisor site with PageSpeed 72 vs. advisor site with PageSpeed 96. Same services. Same market. Same AUM. Result: 43% better conversion from qualified prospects on fast site. Why? High-net-worth prospects notice speed. Slow site: "This advisor can't manage technology, how will they manage my wealth?" Fast site: competence = confidence. Framer and Webflow deliver 95+. Squarespace averages 85-90. Speed matters for finance.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

